723646f-a.title: Manhattan: Union Square (West) - 17th Street.
723646f-a.text:
Union Square West, at, adjoining and south of the S.W. corner of
17th Street.
About 1913.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

717325f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 17th Street
717325f-a.text:
862-868 Broadway, east side, between 17th and 18th Streets.
June 7, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

731171f-a.title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal Events - Communist Demonstration.
731171f-a.text:
Communist Demonstration: A set of three views of the school contingent
making an eastward turn on East 17th Street from Broadway to pass the
reviewing stand in the northern confine of Union Square.
May 1, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

731172f-a.title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal Events - Communist Demonstration.
731172f-a.text:
Communist Demonstration: Three views of the line of march turning
eastward at Broadway and East 17th Street. Views 1 and 2 show an
educational unit while No. 3, a medical group. Note the cooperation
of the New York Police Department.
May 1, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
